    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="520"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d520">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.50/8–2344</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Soviet Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gromyko</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-27">September 27,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: It has been increasingly clear
                    that economic cooperation between the European nations becomes essential <pb
                        facs="0635" n="625" xml:id="pg_625"/> as they are liberated. The United
                    States Government has been asked by the British Government to express its views
                    upon the establishment of a European Economic Committee composed of
                    representatives of the European Allies under the joint guidance of the Soviet
                    Socialist Republics, the United Kingdom, and the United States.</p>
                <p>The British Government has proposed that if the United States Government approves
                    of the suggestion, the Soviet Union be consulted and arrangements made for
                    informal consultation between the three governments.</p>
                <p>A copy of the <hi rend="italic">Aide-Mémoire</hi> which is being currently
                    delivered to the British Government is transmitted herewith.<note n="18"
                        xml:id="d520fn18">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> In this <hi rend="italic"
                        >Aide-Mémoire</hi> the suggestion is made that consultation take place at
                    the earliest possible date upon the matters therein proposed. It is hoped that
                    the Soviet Socialist Republics will concur in this suggestion.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cordell Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
